Christopher J. Kempczinski: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 25, 2017 6:27 AM ET
Hotels, Restaurants and Leisure

Company Overview of McDonald's Corporation



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Christopher J. Kempczinski  President of USA, McDonald's CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 3 different industries.48--As of Fiscal Year 2015
Background

		Mr. Christopher J. Kempczinski, also known as Chris, has been President of USA at McDonald's Corporation since January 1, 2017. Mr. Kempczinski has been President at McDonald's USA, LLC since January 01, 2017. He served as Executive Vice President of Strategy, Business Development & Innovation at McDonald's Corporation since October 26, 2015 until December 2016. Mr. Kempczinski oversaw all aspects of strategy development, planning, innovation and new concepts to drive ... growth for the company. Mr. Kempczinski served as the President of International and Executive Vice President of Growth Initiatives at Kraft Foods Group, Inc., since February 12, 2015 until September, 2015. Mr. Kempczinski served as the President of Kraft Canada Inc since July 2012 until February 12, 2015. He served as an Executive Vice President at Kraft Foods Group, Inc since January 29, 2014 until February 2015. He leads Kraft’s Canadian business unit overseeing all aspects of supply chain, sales, marketing, human resources and research, development and quality. He has full P&L responsibility for the business including beloved brands such as Kraft Dinner, Kraft Peanut Butter, Cracker Barrel natural cheeses and Nabob coffee. During his time with Kraft Canada, Mr. Kempczinski has led the business unit through transformative change with the separation from Mondelez International in October 2012 and later restructuring the organization’s resources to focus on simplification and innovation. Mr. Kempczinski joined Kraft in 2008 as Senior Vice President overseeing brands in the meals and enhancers categories with iconic brands like Kraft Macaroni & Cheese and Kraft dressings. Prior to joining Kraft, he served as Vice President of Marketing in the non-carbonated beverages sector of PepsiCo. Before PepsiCo, he was a Management Consultant at The Boston Consulting Group, focusing predominantly on consumer products and pharmaceuticals. He spent the first four years of his career as a brand manager at Procter & Gamble. He has received numerous marketing awards including 4 Cannes Lions, 2 Emmy nominations and multiple Effie and Clio awards. For his marketing accomplishments, he was inducted into the American Advertising Federation’s Hall of Achievement. Mr. Kempczinski received his B.A. in Economics from Duke University and his MBA from the Harvard Business School.Read Full Background




