Christopher J. (Chris) Kempczinski 

		
		President, McDonald's USA, 

	
		 McDonald's Corporation 	

 
Last Updated: 06/18/2017 



Executive Summary
Kempczinski is President of McDonald's USA at McDonald's Corporation, a role he assumed in January 2017. Most recently he was Executive Vice President of Strategy, Business Development and Innovation at the company, a role to which he was named in 2015. Prior to joining McDonald's, Kem 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Kempczinski has received numerous marketing awards including 4 Cannes Lions, 2 Emmy nominations, and multiple Effie and Clio awards.
For his marketing accomplishments, he was inducted into the American Advertising Federati 
Current Focus

Use Snapchat to attract jobseekers: McDonald’s is turning to Snapchat in a bid to hire more workers, according to a June 2017 Nation’s Restaurant News article. McDonald’s and its franchisees expec 
Biographical Highlights

Kempczinski earned a bachelor’s degree in public policy and economics from Duke University (1987-1991) and an MBA from Harvard Business School (1995-1997).
Brand Manager, Procter & Gamble Company (1991-1995) 
 





